    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/8–2844:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-28T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 28, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3203. I understand that the Rumanian representatives may arrive in Moscow
                    tomorrow August 29. In addition to his instructions on specific points the
                    British Ambassador has been instructed to use the Bulgarian terms as drafted by
                    the European Advisory Commission<note n="90" xml:id="d217fn1">See telegram 6928,
                        August 25, midnight, from London, <ref target="frus1944v03#pg_367">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 367</ref>.</note> as a model. I
                    request urgent instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
